properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 10 at 3:17PM EST until January 12 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 20 to 30 knots with gusts up to 40 knots.
Seas 7 to 10 feet.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague
VA out 20 nm, Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore
Island VA out 20 nm and Coastal waters from Parramore Island
to Cape Charles Light VA out 20 nm.

* WHEN...From Saturday evening through Sunday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY EVENING THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING
